From: tawc
Origin: own

Replace the AOSP-only `nativewindow` Rust crate in
src/gfxstream.rs's PLATFORM_AHB export branch with an embedder hook.
The crate wraps libnativewindow.so APIs and is only published inside
AOSP, so rutabaga does not build outside AOSP with the gfxstream
feature enabled.

The hook is what lets the tawc compositor satisfy kumquat's
RESOURCE_CREATE_BLOB protocol contract (the response is *required*
to ship one fd via SCM_RIGHTS for every PLATFORM_AHB). The
compositor's registered callback dlsym's
`AHardwareBuffer_getNativeHandle` out of `libnativewindow.so`,
walks the handle, dups out the AHB's backing dmabuf fd, and
returns it. The wrapper here boxes that into a MesaHandle of type
MEM_DMABUF so the kumquat layer can ship it via SCM_RIGHTS unchanged.

For host-visible Vulkan memory the chroot mmaps the fd to access the
host allocation. Swapchain images are displayed through the separate
`tawc_gfxstream` ColorBuffer-id path; this hook only satisfies the
kumquat blob response's fd contract.

With no callback set, the branch falls back to InvalidResourceId --
that's the right answer for the bin'd `kumquat` binary, which has
no AHB consumer wired up.

